WEBVTT

00:00:01.040 --> 00:00:02.160
Prae.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:06.320
Please marry Wichan.

00:00:06.920 --> 00:00:09.000
But I don't love Mr. Wichan anymore.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:10.880
I love you.

00:00:10.960 --> 00:00:12.560
I love you too, Prae.

00:00:12.640 --> 00:00:14.040
I love you very much.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:17.720
Shall we go now, Mr. Rut?

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:25.720
Hello, Ms. Praewilai.

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:56.280
Please don't do this again.

00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:59.880
If you want to go somewhere,
tell me first. I won't stop you.

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.080
If it could be like that, it'd be good.

00:03:03.160 --> 00:03:04.880
Then it has to be like that.

00:03:05.480 --> 00:03:08.280
I won't let you go anywhere alone

00:03:08.360 --> 00:03:10.320
and have something like this happen again.

00:03:11.320 --> 00:03:12.280
Thank you.

00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:13.760
Yes.

00:03:14.280 --> 00:03:16.240
-Nong.
-Yes?

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:23.320
If I were to talk about Warat
with Sin, what do you think?

00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:25.080
What did you say?

00:03:25.160 --> 00:03:28.400
Sin is the vengeful type.

00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:31.480
All he thinks about
is destroying the Vanich family.

00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:33.400
I'm afraid.

00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:36.440
Afraid he might hurt Warat.

00:03:46.920 --> 00:03:49.400
If you're thinking of doing that
to protect Warat,

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:53.400
I think it won't work.

00:03:54.600 --> 00:03:58.040
Don't forget that even if Sin knows

00:03:58.120 --> 00:04:01.920
Warat is really your son,
he won't change his mind.

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:03.640
The person he truly hates

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:06.320
is Praewilai, Warat's mother.

00:04:06.400 --> 00:04:09.720
What if I offer

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:15.360
half of Warat's share
of the assets to Sin?

00:04:19.279 --> 00:04:21.560
Why would Sin take just half,

00:04:21.640 --> 00:04:24.760
when he clearly has
the right to take everything?

00:04:24.840 --> 00:04:25.760
Nong.

00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:27.960
How many times do I have to tell you?

00:04:28.040 --> 00:04:29.600
I will never let that happen.

00:04:31.320 --> 00:04:33.000
Don't get angry yet.

00:04:33.080 --> 00:04:36.200
Calm down. No matter what,

00:04:36.280 --> 00:04:38.680
I'm on your side.

00:04:40.440 --> 00:04:43.160
I will try to talk Sin into it.

00:04:44.160 --> 00:04:47.880
The best way is
to make those two reconcile.

00:04:49.160 --> 00:04:51.960
Sin gets his share,

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:55.520
and Mr. Warat gets what belongs to him.

00:04:55.600 --> 00:04:58.320
If it could be like that,
it would be wonderful.

00:04:59.720 --> 00:05:01.960
Then I could finally die in peace.

00:05:03.440 --> 00:05:05.280
I understand.

00:05:06.360 --> 00:05:07.480
Thank you.

00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:11.800
Rest now, please. Take your medicine.

00:05:37.760 --> 00:05:39.240
You heard it, didn't you?

00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:44.240
So we just keep doing our part.

00:05:44.320 --> 00:05:46.040
I'm not telling you to stop.

00:05:46.120 --> 00:05:48.320
And I still insist

00:05:48.920 --> 00:05:53.080
I'll do everything to let Naree,
your mother, rest in peace.

00:05:53.160 --> 00:05:56.360
Even if you hadn't said anything,
I'd still do it anyway.

00:05:56.440 --> 00:05:59.480
For now, just do what Uncle Rut wants.

00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:04.960
And the day Warat gets everything
from Vanich Mall,

00:06:05.040 --> 00:06:06.920
that day will be ours.

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:08.920
If I hadn't heard everything today,

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:11.440
it would've been hard for me
to bring myself to do it.

00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:14.960
That's why I wanted you to hear it
straight from Mr. Rut's mouth.

00:06:16.640 --> 00:06:17.920
Alright, Auntie.

00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:22.960
Mrs. Wanee already adores me.
The more I support Warat,

00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:24.440
the more she'll trust me.

00:06:24.520 --> 00:06:26.200
So,

00:06:26.280 --> 00:06:30.240
you handle everything
on your side as much as you can.

00:06:30.840 --> 00:06:32.400
It's a win-win for us, Auntie.

00:06:37.680 --> 00:06:41.000
Aunt Nong, I really hate
coming around here. It smells so bad.

00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:46.440
That's the smell of my flowers.

00:06:46.520 --> 00:06:47.800
What, Sin?

00:06:47.880 --> 00:06:50.920
You've smelled it since you were a kid
and you're still not used to it?

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:53.520
Auntie, that's clearly a rotting smell.

00:06:54.640 --> 00:06:56.200
I can't take it anymore. I'm leaving.

00:07:15.520 --> 00:07:16.440
You sure you can drive?

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:18.960
If I say I can, then I can.

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:22.480
I usually don't drive
because I have my reasons.

00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:23.680
And the reason is?

00:07:23.760 --> 00:07:27.200
Uh, I'll tell you later.

00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:29.400
But for now, can you check the pin

00:07:29.480 --> 00:07:32.800
for Grandma Aom's house again?
See if there's another route.

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:35.240
I think there's an accident up ahead.

00:07:35.320 --> 00:07:37.400
We should change routes.

00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:41.840
There, see? One already.

00:07:47.320 --> 00:07:48.160
What did you see?

00:07:49.200 --> 00:07:51.560
Nothing. Nothing at all.

00:07:54.480 --> 00:07:57.200
Hey, Kluay, you're driving.
Why are you closing your eyes?

00:07:58.760 --> 00:08:01.600
-I'm sending merit.
-Huh?

00:08:01.680 --> 00:08:03.000
Sending merit?

00:08:03.600 --> 00:08:06.640
Yes. When I drive,

00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:09.920
I have to concentrate a lot.
And I'll see things…

00:08:17.400 --> 00:08:19.920
And when I see things,

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:23.440
I have to send merit.
Sometimes it works, but I have to do it.

00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:25.400
So what do you see now?

00:08:25.480 --> 00:08:27.480
Full force.

00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:36.320
Pull over. I'll take off the cast.

00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:37.600
Are you sure?

00:08:37.679 --> 00:08:40.360
Of course.
You're driving with your eyes closed.

00:08:40.960 --> 00:08:43.720
I'm not risking my life. Pull over.

00:08:45.200 --> 00:08:46.120
Okay.

00:09:06.120 --> 00:09:09.440
Don't go looking for them again.
They'll think you want to see them.

00:09:09.520 --> 00:09:11.440
Don't scold me.

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:13.720
I don't want to see them at all.

00:09:13.800 --> 00:09:15.080
Honestly,

00:09:15.800 --> 00:09:18.880
your special power is pretty cool.

00:09:20.160 --> 00:09:23.000
It comes and goes whenever it wants.

00:09:23.960 --> 00:09:27.720
You see things all the time.
It's a miracle you haven't died of shock.

00:09:29.440 --> 00:09:31.600
Thank you for the blessing.

00:09:33.120 --> 00:09:35.080
But about Ms. Mysterious,

00:09:35.160 --> 00:09:39.120
I've figured out the pattern.
I need to touch you,

00:09:39.200 --> 00:09:42.880
or touch something related to the past
to see visions.

00:09:43.480 --> 00:09:45.200
You need concentration too, right?

00:09:46.840 --> 00:09:48.360
You learn fast.

00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:50.200
Are you being sarcastic?

00:09:51.640 --> 00:09:53.160
But when you…

00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:57.200
took off my cast,
you didn't see anything, did you?

00:09:57.280 --> 00:10:00.760
How do you know I didn't?
Maybe I did, but I just didn't tell you.

00:10:00.840 --> 00:10:04.080
Someone like you
wouldn't be able to lie to anyone.

00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:06.280
You talk like you know me so well.

00:10:06.360 --> 00:10:09.040
Then try telling me.
What kind of person am I?

00:10:09.120 --> 00:10:12.560
I don't waste time meddling
in other people's lives. I'm busy.

00:10:14.160 --> 00:10:15.640
Alright.

00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:19.400
Ugh, again.

00:10:19.480 --> 00:10:22.800
Here we go again.

00:10:23.720 --> 00:10:25.680
Ugh.

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:30.680
It's okay, it's okay. Don't be scared.

00:10:34.560 --> 00:10:35.400
Are they gone?

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:40.840
Are they gone?

00:10:42.320 --> 00:10:43.680
They're gone.

00:10:51.040 --> 00:10:52.400
It's around here.

00:10:52.480 --> 00:10:54.120
But the house number doesn't match.

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:57.200
What do you expect
from the location on the phone?

00:10:57.280 --> 00:10:59.720
Let's just get out and ask the locals.

00:11:02.800 --> 00:11:03.800
Where are they?

00:11:05.280 --> 00:11:07.920
The locals you said we'd ask.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:10.320
I'm looking right now. Just a second.

00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:13.680
Hey.

00:11:17.040 --> 00:11:19.520
Excuse me, Grandma.

00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:24.120
Do you happen to know Grandma Aom?

00:11:24.200 --> 00:11:26.560
That's me. I'm Grandma Aom.

00:11:35.680 --> 00:11:38.520
That's great. What a coincidence. I…

00:11:40.840 --> 00:11:42.320
Here we go again, Kluay.

00:11:44.280 --> 00:11:48.680
You can no longer tell
who's a ghost and who's a person?

00:11:51.480 --> 00:11:53.280
Sometimes I can, sometimes I can't.

00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:55.320
Can I really rely on you?

00:11:57.520 --> 00:11:58.920
Thank you.

00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:02.360
She's just a playful old lady.

00:12:02.440 --> 00:12:03.880
You still praise her?

00:12:05.200 --> 00:12:08.520
Let's go. I feel strange.
It's really hot too.

00:12:08.600 --> 00:12:09.720
How can we leave?

00:12:09.800 --> 00:12:13.520
Since we're already here,
I think I'll ask around a bit more.

00:12:50.600 --> 00:12:51.440
What are you smiling at?

00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:54.760
There's only one amulet.

00:12:57.440 --> 00:12:58.560
Oh, right.

00:12:58.640 --> 00:13:00.320
Then let's go together. Come on.

00:13:27.800 --> 00:13:29.400
-Grandma Aom?
-Yes.

00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:31.600
Grandma Aom Thongsawat.

00:13:31.680 --> 00:13:33.240
Her mother's name was Muat Thongsawat,

00:13:33.320 --> 00:13:35.920
and her father was Suan Thongsawat.

00:13:37.120 --> 00:13:38.840
I don't know her.

00:13:39.440 --> 00:13:42.320
But that surname sounds familiar.

00:13:43.360 --> 00:13:47.200
You can try driving
about ten kilometers out of town

00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:50.560
and you'll reach a village.

00:13:51.200 --> 00:13:53.840
People's surnames there start with Thong.

00:13:53.920 --> 00:13:57.360
Thongsawat, Thongkon,

00:13:57.440 --> 00:14:00.040
Thongnamthip. People around there

00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:03.920
all have Thong surnames.

00:14:04.840 --> 00:14:06.160
Thank… Oh.

00:14:06.760 --> 00:14:08.000
Thank you.

00:14:09.360 --> 00:14:11.920
Ten kilometers?
No way I'm going along with that.

00:14:12.920 --> 00:14:15.960
And we still have to ask around
about Grandma Aom. I think it'll be late.

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:20.280
Then stay here for a night.

00:14:24.760 --> 00:14:27.320
How did he hear that?
Is that a person or what?

00:14:27.400 --> 00:14:31.360
He's a person. It's nothing.
He probably just wants customers.

00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:35.120
Honestly, staying one night sounds fine.

00:14:35.200 --> 00:14:38.680
Help support them a bit.
With the economy like this,

00:14:40.320 --> 00:14:42.200
just surviving is impressive enough.

00:14:42.280 --> 00:14:45.400
Okay then, let's flip a coin.

00:14:45.480 --> 00:14:49.280
If it's heads, we stay here and deal with
Grandma Aom first thing in the morning.

00:14:49.360 --> 00:14:51.760
If it's tails, we go back to Bangkok first

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:54.200
and drive back again tomorrow morning.

00:14:54.280 --> 00:14:56.000
So you want me to go back
to being the same again?

00:14:56.080 --> 00:14:57.600
Take the cast off, put it back on.

00:14:57.680 --> 00:15:00.560
You go back to seeing ghosts again.
Just thinking about it is exhausting.

00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:05.760
Alright, heads it is.
Let's get it over with.

00:15:06.280 --> 00:15:07.520
We're staying here.

00:15:16.880 --> 00:15:17.920
Hey.

00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:20.880
Should we change hotels?

00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:25.120
I don't think there's anything.
Don't overthink it.

00:15:26.120 --> 00:15:27.000
What if there's something?

00:15:27.080 --> 00:15:28.680
Don't overthink it.

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:54.960
Your room looks nice.

00:15:56.520 --> 00:15:59.400
Your room is over there, sir.

00:16:00.280 --> 00:16:02.280
The rooms are right next to each other.

00:16:04.360 --> 00:16:07.480
You checked properly, right?
There's no room

00:16:07.560 --> 00:16:10.400
with two beds,
a twin or anything like that?

00:16:10.480 --> 00:16:12.040
No, ma'am.

00:16:12.720 --> 00:16:14.560
They're all fully booked.

00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:15.480
Oh.

00:16:20.040 --> 00:16:21.520
Didn't you say you didn't see anything?

00:16:21.600 --> 00:16:23.920
Not seeing doesn't mean
there's nothing there.

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:26.760
Come on. If anything happens,

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:30.840
you can knock on my door
anytime tonight, okay?

00:16:32.400 --> 00:16:34.680
Mr. Warat, I think

00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:37.560
you should wear the amulet.

00:16:37.640 --> 00:16:38.600
No need.

00:16:39.640 --> 00:16:41.320
You're the one who sees things, not me.

00:16:42.640 --> 00:16:43.800
Good night.

00:17:09.720 --> 00:17:11.839
Wow, that looks really tasty.

00:17:13.839 --> 00:17:17.800
Tell me first who did that to Kluay,
or you don't get to eat.

00:17:17.880 --> 00:17:19.880
I already told you.

00:17:19.960 --> 00:17:21.160
Just some Karen.

00:17:21.240 --> 00:17:23.319
So this is how you're going to be, Arnon?

00:17:23.400 --> 00:17:25.800
Fine. I'll investigate it myself.

00:17:25.880 --> 00:17:28.920
I'll just call the fake news unit

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:31.920
and dig and dig until I find the culprit.

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:33.280
Alright, alright.

00:17:34.960 --> 00:17:36.160
I'll tell you.

00:17:39.040 --> 00:17:43.520
But Kluay told me not to tell anyone.

00:17:43.600 --> 00:17:46.240
See? You lied to me, didn't you?

00:17:46.840 --> 00:17:49.120
-I'll put the whole plate into your mouth.
-Som, Som, don't.

00:17:49.200 --> 00:17:52.080
-Why did you do this? Why lie to me?
-Som, it hurts.

00:17:52.160 --> 00:17:53.880
-I just can't say it.
-What's all the noise?

00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:57.080
Why were you yelling at him like that?

00:17:57.160 --> 00:17:59.520
I can hear you
all the way from the prayer room.

00:17:59.600 --> 00:18:00.680
Hello, Mama Toi.

00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:04.760
You came just in time to help.

00:18:04.840 --> 00:18:06.240
Oh? You're tattling now?

00:18:06.320 --> 00:18:07.840
That's enough, Som.

00:18:09.560 --> 00:18:13.000
Mr. Arnon, don't indulge her too much.

00:18:13.080 --> 00:18:15.960
She plays rough and never holds back.

00:18:16.040 --> 00:18:18.520
Yes, I'll remember that.

00:18:19.480 --> 00:18:22.040
So what's going on?

00:18:22.120 --> 00:18:24.840
Don't tell me it's about Kluay.

00:18:24.920 --> 00:18:26.240
-No, it's nothing.
-No.

00:18:27.560 --> 00:18:29.760
It's really nothing, Mom. Kluay is fine.

00:18:29.840 --> 00:18:33.160
You didn't hear or see anything, did you?

00:18:33.240 --> 00:18:36.080
What happened? What do you mean?

00:18:36.160 --> 00:18:39.400
Som was just asking, just in case.

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:42.160
In case you were missing Ms. Kluay. Right?

00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:44.680
-Yes, yes.
-Yes.

00:18:44.760 --> 00:18:47.440
It's late now. Let him go rest.

00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:49.000
Who tied his legs up?

00:18:49.080 --> 00:18:51.240
He won't go back on his own.

00:18:53.360 --> 00:18:56.280
I'll take my leave then.
Mama Toi, goodbye.

00:18:56.360 --> 00:19:00.000
-Goodbye. Uh, Mr. Arnon.
-Yes?

00:19:00.080 --> 00:19:02.000
Will you come here tomorrow?

00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:04.280
Is there something
you'd like me to help with?

00:19:09.080 --> 00:19:12.000
Let's talk tomorrow. Thank you very much.

00:19:12.080 --> 00:19:15.240
-Alright. Goodbye again.
-Goodbye.

00:19:21.320 --> 00:19:22.640
Wait, Mom.

00:19:24.360 --> 00:19:26.360
What did you want to talk to Arnon about?

00:19:35.280 --> 00:19:37.520
About Kluay.

00:19:37.600 --> 00:19:40.840
I want him to help investigate

00:19:40.920 --> 00:19:43.120
her parents. Uh…

00:19:44.240 --> 00:19:46.720
No, Mom, don't do this.

00:19:46.800 --> 00:19:50.160
Kluay is my sister.
I won't let her go anywhere.

00:19:51.040 --> 00:19:52.720
It's not like that, Som.

00:19:52.800 --> 00:19:55.080
-Listen to me.
-I'm not listening.

00:19:56.040 --> 00:19:57.120
Did you forget

00:19:57.200 --> 00:19:59.840
that Dad died because of things like this?

00:19:59.920 --> 00:20:02.920
I don't want it to happen again.

00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:04.480
I feel sorry for Kluay.

00:20:06.440 --> 00:20:09.080
Som. Som.

00:20:21.840 --> 00:20:23.960
Is this what you call nice?

00:20:25.320 --> 00:20:28.000
Why does Mr. Warat
praise this place so much?

00:20:30.880 --> 00:20:32.400
Please don't let me run into anything.

00:20:52.960 --> 00:20:54.240
It's Mr. Warat's room.

00:20:58.160 --> 00:20:59.440
Who is he talking to?

00:21:05.080 --> 00:21:09.400
Oh, so this is why
he wouldn't let me stay in the same room.

00:21:10.720 --> 00:21:12.040
Uh, why is he like this?

00:21:18.040 --> 00:21:20.840
WARAT

00:21:22.160 --> 00:21:25.400
Hello? You still have time to call me?

00:21:25.480 --> 00:21:27.840
I just realized
what kind of person you are.

00:21:27.920 --> 00:21:31.280
Good. Now you know.
Go wherever you want. Don't bother me.

00:21:31.360 --> 00:21:34.960
What? Mr. Warat,
why are you talking to me like this?

00:21:35.040 --> 00:21:38.120
I'm sick of you. Stay away from me.

00:21:38.200 --> 00:21:39.320
I hate you.

00:21:40.080 --> 00:21:42.840
Hey. Are you out of your mind?

00:21:42.920 --> 00:21:44.720
What did I do to you?

00:21:47.360 --> 00:21:49.040
Hello? Mr. Warat?

00:21:51.200 --> 00:21:52.400
What's wrong with him?

00:21:54.760 --> 00:21:56.880
He didn't have to show the girl
how much he hates me.

00:21:57.480 --> 00:21:58.600
He's crazy.

00:22:05.120 --> 00:22:06.200
Or…

00:22:21.880 --> 00:22:24.200
Uh, what's that plate?

00:22:24.280 --> 00:22:26.800
He ordered food, ma'am.

00:22:29.320 --> 00:22:31.040
Then why are there two plates?

00:22:51.840 --> 00:22:54.200
Why didn't he answer?

00:23:11.720 --> 00:23:14.680
Mr. Arnon.
I'll ask Mr. Arnon to help talk to him.

00:23:22.280 --> 00:23:25.720
Now my battery dies?
And I didn't bring my charger.

00:23:28.400 --> 00:23:29.680
Whoa.

00:23:31.240 --> 00:23:34.080
Excuse me, sorry, is anyone there?

00:23:35.080 --> 00:23:37.920
I'd like to borrow a charger.

00:23:43.360 --> 00:23:44.600
What should I do?

00:23:49.880 --> 00:23:51.400
What should I do?

00:24:05.240 --> 00:24:07.880
Excuse me, sir.

00:24:07.960 --> 00:24:10.600
Are there any shops open around here?

00:24:10.680 --> 00:24:14.040
They're all closed, kid.
People here go to bed early.

00:24:15.800 --> 00:24:17.000
You're from somewhere else?

00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:20.400
Yes, I'm from Bangkok.

00:24:21.080 --> 00:24:22.280
Again?

00:24:26.560 --> 00:24:28.600
What do you mean by that?

00:24:28.680 --> 00:24:32.440
No one stays here.
Only people who get lost wander in.

00:24:32.520 --> 00:24:36.240
If there's a man,
you should go somewhere else if possible.

00:24:36.320 --> 00:24:39.240
-The widow ghost will take his soul.
-Huh?

00:24:39.320 --> 00:24:42.080
-They have ghosts here.
-Huh?

00:25:00.880 --> 00:25:01.880
Mr. Warat.

00:25:08.360 --> 00:25:11.200
Hey, what did you put in my friend's food?

00:25:11.280 --> 00:25:12.760
Why is he knocked out like this?

00:25:15.720 --> 00:25:17.200
I'm asking you. Answer me.

00:25:17.280 --> 00:25:20.640
Do you know this is illegal?

00:25:21.800 --> 00:25:22.960
I'll call the police.

00:25:28.640 --> 00:25:30.680
I'll make sure you pay for this.

00:25:48.160 --> 00:25:50.200
Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat.

00:25:50.280 --> 00:25:51.880
Mr. Warat, can you hear me?

00:25:54.120 --> 00:25:57.040
Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat, can you hear me?

00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:05.040
One, two, three.

00:26:10.160 --> 00:26:11.600
Ow, Mr. Warat.

00:26:13.800 --> 00:26:15.280
How can they do this in movies?

00:26:17.960 --> 00:26:19.000
What do I do now?

00:26:22.560 --> 00:26:23.440
Yes.

00:26:31.680 --> 00:26:34.840
Oh god, this is a total disaster.

00:26:34.920 --> 00:26:38.000
Fighting people in the morning,
fighting ghosts at night.

00:26:38.080 --> 00:26:40.280
You can do it. You can do it.

00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:45.880
Mr. Warat.

00:26:51.880 --> 00:26:53.080
Mr. Warat.

00:26:53.160 --> 00:26:55.760
Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat.

00:26:55.840 --> 00:26:57.760
Mr. Warat, wake up.

00:26:57.840 --> 00:26:59.400
Hey, Mr. Warat.

00:26:59.480 --> 00:27:00.440
Mr. Warat.

00:27:20.240 --> 00:27:21.880
Let's just stay out of each other's lives.

00:27:22.760 --> 00:27:25.120
You have no right to this man.

00:27:26.120 --> 00:27:29.560
The reason you're stuck in this loop
is because you won't stop the karma.

00:27:30.200 --> 00:27:32.720
Go. And I'll make merit for you.

00:27:38.880 --> 00:27:42.280
Mr. Warat, wake up already. Wake up.

00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:49.360
Don't do that. You can't do that.

00:27:53.920 --> 00:27:56.040
He's my husband.

00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:01.440
Go on if…

00:28:01.520 --> 00:28:05.560
you want to receive a full-on punishment
in hell. Do you know

00:28:05.640 --> 00:28:08.520
that stealing someone else's husband
means climbing the spiky fig tree?

00:28:09.520 --> 00:28:11.440
Huh? Still not stopping?

00:28:12.600 --> 00:28:16.160
You still don't believe me, do you?
Fine. Look at this.

00:28:46.520 --> 00:28:48.760
Ugh, why do I
have to do something like this?

00:28:49.880 --> 00:28:50.840
Mr. Warat.

00:28:54.640 --> 00:28:56.280
I told you not to stay here.

00:28:56.360 --> 00:28:59.000
Ow, you ignored me.

00:29:44.560 --> 00:29:45.400
Hey.

00:29:46.680 --> 00:29:48.120
Are you really that scared of ghosts?

00:29:52.880 --> 00:29:53.800
Kluay.

00:29:55.440 --> 00:29:57.040
Kluay, wake up.

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:08.040
Morning? Morning what?

00:30:14.160 --> 00:30:15.240
What's wrong with her?

00:30:22.240 --> 00:30:24.120
Please check it for me.

00:30:24.200 --> 00:30:26.360
I'll write up a report and send it later.

00:30:27.240 --> 00:30:29.600
Okay, thank you very much.

00:30:29.680 --> 00:30:30.800
Just because there's no twin bed,

00:30:31.480 --> 00:30:34.400
you're filing a complaint
against the hotel?

00:30:34.480 --> 00:30:36.680
Yes. I can't let it slide.

00:30:36.760 --> 00:30:38.720
You're really something, you know that?

00:30:39.480 --> 00:30:41.920
Didn't you say
you didn't want trouble with anyone?

00:30:42.800 --> 00:30:46.080
With people, yes.
But with ghosts, I'm not so sure.

00:30:48.720 --> 00:30:50.000
You still haven't told me.

00:30:50.680 --> 00:30:54.360
Why did you come sleep
in my room last night?

00:30:55.240 --> 00:30:56.800
You still have the nerve to ask?

00:30:56.880 --> 00:30:58.720
You're so charming, aren't you?

00:30:59.880 --> 00:31:01.880
Why take your anger
at the hotel out on me?

00:31:03.920 --> 00:31:04.920
Don't tell me

00:31:05.520 --> 00:31:07.400
you did something to me last night.

00:31:17.320 --> 00:31:19.800
What? Are you crazy?
What could I possibly do to you?

00:31:19.880 --> 00:31:24.040
I was just scared of ghosts, so I went
to sleep in your room. That's it.

00:31:25.400 --> 00:31:26.440
We're here.

00:31:26.520 --> 00:31:29.560
The intersection up ahead
is the entrance to Grandma Aom's village.

00:31:42.360 --> 00:31:46.000
I'm sorry, Mom,
for not calling ahead first.

00:31:46.080 --> 00:31:50.560
I thought Mr. Warat had returned home,
so I stopped by.

00:31:50.640 --> 00:31:51.920
It's alright.

00:31:52.960 --> 00:31:55.400
Rat only called to tell me last night

00:31:55.480 --> 00:31:58.240
that he'd be staying overnight
at the worksite in Hua Hin.

00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:02.920
And when I saw that
Kluay went with him, I felt at ease.

00:32:03.000 --> 00:32:05.160
That's good, very good, Mom.

00:32:05.240 --> 00:32:07.400
Ms. Kluay is helping look after him.

00:32:07.480 --> 00:32:11.400
With Mr. Warat's business background
and Kluay assisting with so many things,

00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:14.640
I think many good things
will happen for Vanich.

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:19.520
Still, I can't help worrying a little.

00:32:19.600 --> 00:32:22.560
You're all still new.

00:32:24.000 --> 00:32:25.440
Most importantly,

00:32:25.520 --> 00:32:27.640
you need to take it slow.

00:32:27.720 --> 00:32:31.640
Adjust gradually.
Forgive each other when things get rough.

00:32:32.840 --> 00:32:33.880
Yes, Mom.

00:32:33.960 --> 00:32:36.120
Seeing this,

00:32:36.200 --> 00:32:38.240
I feel relieved.

00:32:39.240 --> 00:32:41.960
Thank you, Sin, for looking out for Warat.

00:32:43.040 --> 00:32:43.840
Yes.

00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:49.640
I feel the same as you do, Supol.

00:32:49.720 --> 00:32:51.640
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

00:32:51.720 --> 00:32:53.640
I wouldn't have thought
much of it before this.

00:32:53.720 --> 00:32:57.800
But once I learned that Mr. Jirasin
is connected to Mr. Sarut and his wife,

00:32:57.880 --> 00:33:02.080
I felt we should perhaps
keep an eye on them, shouldn't we?

00:33:02.160 --> 00:33:05.400
When we took Jirasin and his sister

00:33:05.480 --> 00:33:08.520
into the care of the Vanich Fund,

00:33:08.600 --> 00:33:11.640
no relatives ever showed up.

00:33:11.720 --> 00:33:13.320
Yes, ma'am.

00:33:13.400 --> 00:33:15.640
And now, Mr. Sarut, his uncle-in-law

00:33:15.720 --> 00:33:20.360
and Ms. Anong, his biological aunt,
have suddenly appeared. That's why I think

00:33:20.440 --> 00:33:23.840
we should observe them a bit longer.

00:33:24.480 --> 00:33:26.880
But there are positive signs.

00:33:26.960 --> 00:33:30.200
Sin has shown kindness.

00:33:30.280 --> 00:33:32.600
He even brought gifts to visit Rat here.

00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:39.240
I'm very tired already.

00:33:40.160 --> 00:33:44.640
If there's something
we can compromise on, let's do it.

00:33:44.720 --> 00:33:48.080
If it helps put my mind at ease

00:33:48.160 --> 00:33:51.520
and lets the younger generation
take over Vanich,

00:33:52.720 --> 00:33:54.880
that would be good for me.

00:33:55.640 --> 00:33:56.960
Yes, ma'am.

00:34:14.920 --> 00:34:15.880
Hello.

00:34:18.840 --> 00:34:21.239
After quitting work
at a wealthy household in Bangkok,

00:34:21.320 --> 00:34:24.120
Grandma Aom moved here
over twenty years ago.

00:34:24.199 --> 00:34:26.679
At that time, I was working in the city

00:34:26.760 --> 00:34:28.679
and didn't know much about her.

00:34:28.760 --> 00:34:30.920
You can talk to her yourselves.

00:34:34.080 --> 00:34:36.600
-Thank you.
-She should be awake by now.

00:34:37.520 --> 00:34:38.800
Careful, Grandma.

00:34:41.040 --> 00:34:42.000
Oh, Grandma.

00:34:52.320 --> 00:34:56.719
Mr. Warat, are you doing well?

00:34:56.800 --> 00:34:59.560
And did Madam come too?

00:35:00.240 --> 00:35:01.880
It's just the two of us.

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:05.240
You know me too, Grandma?

00:35:05.840 --> 00:35:07.520
Of course I do.

00:35:09.080 --> 00:35:12.720
You're… Mr. Warat.

00:35:14.400 --> 00:35:16.400
And this is …

00:35:18.720 --> 00:35:19.880
Miss…

00:35:21.360 --> 00:35:24.000
Thank you so much for coming all this way.

00:35:24.640 --> 00:35:27.920
If Som knew,
she'd definitely be angry with you.

00:35:28.840 --> 00:35:31.520
Don't worry about her. I can handle it.

00:35:31.600 --> 00:35:36.640
Alright, I'll get straight to the point.
So you don't have to waste your time.

00:35:36.720 --> 00:35:37.600
Sure.

00:35:38.920 --> 00:35:41.760
It's about Kluay.

00:35:41.840 --> 00:35:45.360
Honestly,
I'm not comfortable doing this either,

00:35:45.440 --> 00:35:48.040
since she's already an adult.

00:35:48.120 --> 00:35:50.600
I'm worried it might violate her rights.

00:35:51.240 --> 00:35:52.720
You can say it first.

00:35:52.800 --> 00:35:54.920
I'll tell you what can and can't be done.

00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:56.640
-Oh, okay.
-Alright.

00:35:59.920 --> 00:36:04.200
Som's dad cared deeply about
the background of every kid who came here.

00:36:04.280 --> 00:36:07.680
He insisted on investigating thoroughly
whether a child truly had no parents

00:36:07.760 --> 00:36:09.760
or guardians.

00:36:09.840 --> 00:36:11.640
All for the child's own benefit.

00:36:11.720 --> 00:36:13.440
That's very admirable.

00:36:14.000 --> 00:36:18.000
But in Kluay's case,
the investigation was never completed

00:36:18.080 --> 00:36:22.040
because he passed away first,
in a car accident.

00:36:22.640 --> 00:36:24.080
I'm very sorry.

00:36:24.160 --> 00:36:25.720
Thank you.

00:36:25.800 --> 00:36:27.480
My husband's friend, a police officer,

00:36:27.560 --> 00:36:31.640
suspected it might have been murder.

00:36:32.440 --> 00:36:36.920
Because my husband had been investigating
a car with a swapped license plate

00:36:37.000 --> 00:36:38.960
involved in the accident
that killed Kluay's parents.

00:36:39.560 --> 00:36:42.040
Your husband believed
it was a staged killing

00:36:42.120 --> 00:36:44.320
of Ms. Kluay's family?

00:36:45.160 --> 00:36:46.200
Yes.

00:36:46.280 --> 00:36:50.480
If that's true, then the perpetrators
must have been very influential,

00:36:50.560 --> 00:36:52.600
or had extremely strong motives.

00:36:54.600 --> 00:36:58.720
That's why his friend
asked me to stop everything,

00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:01.760
out of fear that Som and I
would be targeted.

00:37:02.600 --> 00:37:03.520
That makes sense.

00:37:03.600 --> 00:37:05.600
But there's one thing

00:37:05.680 --> 00:37:07.560
that's been weighing heavily on me.

00:37:07.640 --> 00:37:12.280
I feel that Kluay herself
has the right to know who she really is.

00:37:13.480 --> 00:37:17.160
That's a difficult question
for me too, ma'am.

00:37:21.800 --> 00:37:24.880
This was found on Kluay
when she was brought in.

00:37:24.960 --> 00:37:27.440
I've kept it quietly for a long time.

00:37:32.080 --> 00:37:34.080
An anklet for a child.

00:37:35.040 --> 00:37:37.520
Since Kluay reached adulthood,

00:37:37.600 --> 00:37:40.120
I've been torn

00:37:40.200 --> 00:37:42.080
about whether to return it to her.

00:37:42.160 --> 00:37:46.040
It's like you knew there was a way
to trace Ms. Kluay's past,

00:37:46.120 --> 00:37:49.360
yet you chose to keep it a secret
for everyone's safety.

00:37:50.520 --> 00:37:53.800
I must seem very selfish, right?

00:37:53.880 --> 00:37:56.320
Please don't blame yourself like that.

00:37:56.400 --> 00:37:59.040
Keeping it secret

00:37:59.120 --> 00:38:02.000
was what kept Ms. Kluay safe.

00:38:02.080 --> 00:38:06.080
Who knows,
the people who intended to harm her family

00:38:06.160 --> 00:38:07.760
might still be at large.

00:38:08.600 --> 00:38:10.880
If you or Ms. Kluay made a scene

00:38:10.960 --> 00:38:13.560
trying to track down her family,

00:38:13.640 --> 00:38:16.040
they might strike again.

00:38:16.120 --> 00:38:19.920
Yes. I've thought the same.

00:38:21.040 --> 00:38:22.680
Let's do this.

00:38:22.760 --> 00:38:25.560
I'll try sounding Ms. Kluay out a bit

00:38:25.640 --> 00:38:28.360
and see how she feels about her origins.

00:38:28.960 --> 00:38:31.280
Thank you so much, Mr. Arnon.

00:38:32.320 --> 00:38:33.400
You're welcome.

00:38:37.160 --> 00:38:40.080
Ms. Ampha, you're the mother of…

00:38:40.160 --> 00:38:41.720
NEXT EPISODE

00:38:41.800 --> 00:38:44.360
If Ms. Ampha was not related to me,

00:38:44.440 --> 00:38:46.240
why does she keep following me?

00:38:47.840 --> 00:38:49.600
These fruits

00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:51.800
are from the basket
Mr. Jirasin brought for you yesterday.

00:38:51.880 --> 00:38:53.840
What are you doing, Boonsita?

00:38:55.000 --> 00:38:56.240
Mr. Warat, where are you going?

00:38:58.720 --> 00:39:00.200
Dad and Ms. Ampha are right here.

00:39:00.280 --> 00:39:03.400
That's not true. Get a grip.

00:41:28.120 --> 00:41:30.120
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon